{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place parsley into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer into a bowl and place into refrigerator until needed. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil, lemon juice, chilli flakes, paprika and 1 teaspoon of the salt and heat <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a sealable sterilised jar or bottle and set aside to cool completely, then seal. Set aside to infuse (see Tips).","Place prawns into a large bowl, add half of the reserved oil (approx. 125 g) and toss well to coat. Place into refrigerator for a minimum of 30 minutes (up to 3 hours) to marinate.","Place water into mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket and weigh rice into it. Add remaining 1 teaspoon salt and cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 4<b>.","Divide prawns between Varoma dish and tray. Place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>.","Stir with spatula to ensure even cooking, then secure Varoma lid and steam <b>3-5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, until prawns are cooked to your liking. Transfer prawns into a bowl, add reserved parsley butter and toss to coat. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer rice onto a large serving plate. Place prawns on top of rice, drizzle with a few tablespoons of the reserved oil and serve with remaining oil and lemon wedges."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","20 g salted butter","3 garlic cloves","200 g oil","2 tbsp lemon juice","2 - 3 tsp dried chilli flakes","2 tsp paprika","2 tsp salt","24 large raw prawns (approx. 500 g), deveined, butterflied, shells and heads intact (see Tips)","600 g water","250 g long grain white rice","lemon wedges, to serve"]}],"id":"r145107","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-nNsyPAb3rDM\/XZMuz2uLiJI\/AAAAAAAAaKA\/3tOt3P-nApomv5Covn1uyEp-yLeFXtukQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_SGhPNAM1LsT34RSG.png","title":"Chilli and garlic prawns","publishedAt":"2017-07-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"30.5 g","fat":"55.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"51.1 g","calories":"3495 kJ \/ 832 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, sealable sterilised jar, large bowl, large serving plate, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Ask your fishmonger to devein and butterfly your prawns for you.","The chilli oil can be made up to 1 week in advance and stored in the refrigerator to boost flavour and colours."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 10m","4 portions"]}